<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Paris Jackson put on a very leggy display, after enjoying dinner with a male pal at San Vicente Bungalow in West Hollywood on Friday night. </p>

<p>The 22-year-old singer looked in high spirits, as she strutted around in the shortest of denim shorts, which were almost entirely camouflaged under her tie-dye sweatshirt.</p>

<p>After exiting the private social club, which is reserved for around 750 highly vetted members, the pair chatted under their face masks at the valet.  </p>

<p>Keeping it casual: Paris Jackson put on a very leggy display, after enjoying dinner with a male pal at San Vicente Bungalow in West Hollywood on Friday night</p>

<p>She appeared to be embracing the ultra-exclusive club's no dress code policy, by pairing her relaxed ensemble with a pair of white sneakers and her hair in a bun. </p>

<p>Additionally, the daughter of the late Michael Jackson showcased a few of her known 50 tattoos, including a cactus and skull on her ankle. </p>

<p>Earlier this month, news broke that she and her boyfriend Gabriel Glenn split after more than two years together. </p>

<p>All legs: The 22-year-old singer looked in high spirits, as she strutted around in the shortest of denim shorts, which were almost entirely camouflaged under her tie-dye sweatshirt</p>

<p>According to TMZ, the breakup between Paris and the 23-year-old musician is said to have been 'amicable.'  </p>

<p>The pair attracted attention after their Facebook Watch series 'Unfiltered: Paris Jackson and Gabriel Glenn' - aired earlier this month- and revealed that she once lived in a van with her now ex-boyfriend shortly after meeting him.</p>

<p>It was also revealed in an episode that the pair were 'constantly butting heads,' but sources told TMZ the former lovebirds don't hold 'any anger or ill will.'</p>

<p>It's over: Paris had been in a relationship with Gabriel for two years, as well as serving as her bandmate in The Soundflowers; seen in 2018</p>

<p>Per the report, it was Paris who made the decision to separate, and now wants to concentrate on her music career.</p>

<p>'A big thing for Aries is we are very impatient, depending on what it is,' Paris said on the show. 'The people that we love and things that we care about, we have the patience of a saint.'</p>

<p>'But it's a very interesting dynamic. We both have double stubborn energy. I've always known I was stubborn, and I knew that he was stubborn because he’s a Taurus.' </p>

<p>Making music: Two days ago, she shared a snap of herself in the studio with a guitar for her nearly four million Instagram followers </p>

<p>Two days ago, she shared a two snaps of herself in the studio with a guitar for her nearly four million Instagram followers. </p>

<p>Paris captioned the photos with Manchester Orchestra's Andy Hull, 'thank you for the most incredible and unforgettable experience.'</p>

<p>'It was an absolute honour to create with you guys, especially on a project so vulnerable and raw and close to my heart. I poured my soul into these songs when I wrote them, and you guys took it to a level I could have never even imagined,' she said, while also tagging Robert Mcdowell, Jamie Martens, Dan Hannon. </p>

<p>She concluded: 'The kindness, thoughtfulness, and love you guys exhibited is beyond my ability to describe. Not to mention it’s rare and a total privilege for an amateur musician to be able to say she got to work with her heroes on her first album. I am eternally grateful.'   </p>

<p>Grateful: Paris captioned a photo with Manchester Orchestra's Andy Hull, 'thank you for the most incredible and unforgettable experience'</p>
